. Dadurch wird sowohl juristischen Fachleuten als auch Laien ein transparentes Analysemodell der Rechtskommunikation unterbreitet.  aUsing linguistic instruments this work sets out to give a transparent description of the text-supported and discourse-based legal dispute in the process of reaching a legal judgement. It examines a corpus of authentic texts originating from six related legal cases in Germany, identifying distinct speech act patterns and the specific action strategies and perspective-defining efforts that are used with them. With their help a model is developed for the analysis of this specialized communication process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunication in lawzGermany. 0aLawzGermanyxLanguage. 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aPerspektivität. 4aRechtssprache. 4aTextlinguistik. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / German.2bisacsh  aDiscourse Analysis.  aLegal Terminology.  aPerspectivity.  aTextlinguistics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311026315240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311026316940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110263169423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110263169/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2011  aZDB-23-DGGb2011  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014